Bookmark++
**********

Bookmark++ is a fork of Drew Adams' Bookmark+ package, updated for GNU
Emacs 30 and later.  As the original Bookmark+, Bookmark++ extends the
built-in functionality of ‘bookmark.el’ with over 70 bookmark types,
tagging, a rich ‘*Bmkp List*’ browse buffer, multiple bookmark files,
region bookmarks, persistent per-bookmark highlighting, live preview,
and more.

   This manual is for users of GNU Emacs 30 or later.  It assumes you
are already familiar with the basics of GNU Emacs (buffers, files,
keymaps, the minibuffer).  *Note Migration::, if you are coming from
upstream Bookmark+ and want a summary of what changed in this fork.

