4.1 Prefix Keys
===============

Bookmark+ allocates dedicated prefix keys for bookmarking, separate from
the shared ‘C-x r’ register prefix.

Keymap                    Default     Purpose
                          key
---------------------------------------------------------------------------
‘bookmark-map’            ‘C-x x’     General bookmark commands.
‘bmkp-set-map’            ‘C-x x c’   Create (set) new bookmarks.
‘bmkp-tags-map’           ‘C-x x t’   Tag commands.
‘bmkp-annotate-map’       ‘C-x x a’   Annotation commands.
‘bmkp-jump-map’           ‘C-x j’     Jump (visit) bookmarks (same
                                      window).
‘bmkp-jump-other-window-map’‘C-x 4 j’ Jump (other window).
built-in other-frame      ‘C-x 5 j’   Jump (other frame).
jump

   These prefixes are themselves customizable through three list-valued
options:

‘bmkp-bookmark-map-prefix-keys’
     Default ‘(list (kbd "C-x x"))’.
‘bmkp-jump-map-prefix-keys’
     Default ‘(list (kbd "C-x j"))’.
‘bmkp-jump-other-window-map-prefix-keys’
     Default ‘(list (kbd "C-x 4 j"))’.

   Because they are lists, you can bind a keymap under several prefixes
at once.  The setter function rebinds the keys automatically when you
customize.


