4.2 Binding Bookmark+ to the Standard Keys
==========================================

Loading Bookmark+ does not redefine any built-in command.  If you want
‘C-x r m’, ‘C-x r b’, ‘C-x r l’ to run the Bookmark+ versions, add this
to your init file:

     (define-key bookmark-map "m" #'bmkp-bookmark-set-confirm-overwrite)
     (define-key bookmark-map "b" #'bmkp-jump)
     (define-key bookmark-map "l" #'bmkp-list)

   If you also want programmatic callers (‘consult-bookmark’,
‘helm-bookmark’, Org-mode bookmark links, etc.)  to pick up Bookmark+'s
enhancements when they invoke ‘bookmark-jump’, add:

     (advice-add 'bookmark-jump :override #'bmkp-jump)

   No helper command is required.  These are plain Emacs primitives;
remove the lines (or call ‘advice-remove’) to reverse them.


