                                                marked.
‘bmkp-bmenu-describe-this+move-down’‘C-<down>’  Move + describe.
‘bmkp-bmenu-describe-this+move-up’‘C-<up>’      Same, going up.

7.12 Defining Commands From the View
====================================

‘C-c C-c’
     ‘bmkp-bmenu-define-command’--define a command that restores the
     current display state (sort/filter/etc.).
‘C-c C-S-c’
     ‘bmkp-bmenu-define-full-snapshot-command’--restores the full
     bookmark list including marks.  Larger but complete.
‘C-c C-j’
     ‘bmkp-bmenu-define-jump-marked-command’--a type-specific jump
     command whose candidates are the marked bookmarks.

   Defined commands are appended to ‘bmkp-bmenu-commands-file’, which is
loaded automatically on first opening ‘*Bmkp List*’.

7.13 Preview Mode
=================

‘M-p’ (‘bmkp-list-preview-mode’) toggles live preview of the bookmark on
point.  *Note Live Preview::, for details.

7.14 Casual Menu
================

‘c’ (‘casual-bmkp-tmenu’) opens a Transient-based menu UI if the
‘casual-lib’ package is installed.  *Note Casual Integration::.


