13 Live Preview
***************

Live preview shows the bookmark's destination without committing to a
jump.  Two surfaces are provided.

13.1 In ‘*Bmkp List*’: ‘bmkp-list-preview-mode’
===============================================

A buffer-local minor mode in ‘*Bmkp List*’, modeled on the built-in
‘next-error-follow-minor-mode’.  Toggle with ‘M-p’.

   When the mode is enabled:

   • Moving point onto a bookmark line opens its destination in another
     window, without changing the selected window.
   • The mode-line lighter is ‘ Pv’.
   • The window configuration is captured on mode-entry and restored on
     mode-exit.

   The display action used to show the destination is governed by
‘bmkp-list-preview-display-action’ (default: some other window,
‘inhibit-same-window’).

13.2 On Demand: ‘C-o’ and <TAB>
===============================

In ‘*Bmkp List*’, ‘C-o’ and <TAB> both invoke
‘bmkp-list-switch-other-window’: open the bookmark in another window,
leaving the cursor in the list buffer.  Useful for one-off peeking
without entering the full preview mode.

13.3 In the Minibuffer: consult Integration
===========================================

When the ‘consult’ package is loaded and ‘bmkp-preview-use-consult-flag’
is non-nil (the default), the interactive bookmark-name read for
‘bmkp-jump’ (and its other-window and other-frame variants) is routed
through ‘consult--read’ with ‘consult--bookmark-preview’ as the ‘:state’
callback--the same mechanism ‘consult-bookmark’ uses.  You get live
preview as you move through completion candidates.

   If ‘consult’ is not loaded, the read falls back to plain
‘bmkp-completing-read’--no behavior change.


