16 Automatic Bookmarking
************************

16.1 On a Hook
==============

Add ‘bmkp-set-automatic-bookmark’ to any hook to create a bookmark
whenever that hook runs:

     (add-hook 'imenu-after-jump-hook #'bmkp-set-automatic-bookmark)

   The bookmark created is an autonamed bookmark.

16.2 Idle-Period Bookmarking
============================

‘bmkp-automatic-bookmark-mode’ is a buffer-local minor mode that sets an
autonamed bookmark whenever Emacs has been idle for
‘bmkp-automatic-bookmark-mode-delay’ seconds in the current buffer.
‘bmkp-global-automatic-bookmark-mode’ turns it on everywhere (a bookmark
is still only created for the currently selected buffer).

   Tuning options:

   • ‘bmkp-automatic-bookmark-mode-lighter’--mode-line lighter (default
     ‘Auto-Bmk’; set to ‘""’ to hide).
   • ‘bmkp-automatic-bookmark-min-distance’--minimum distance (in
     characters) from the nearest existing automatic bookmark.
   • ‘bmkp-automatic-bookmark-set-function’--which command to use.

16.3 Automatic Info Bookmarking
===============================

Enable ‘bmkp-info-auto-bookmark-mode’ and every Info node you visit
either creates or updates a bookmark named ‘(MANUAL) NODE’.
‘bmkp-info-auto-type’ chooses between ‘update-only’ (default) and
‘create-or-replace’; ‘bmkp-toggle-info-auto-type’ flips it.

   The result is a persistent log of "what I have read recently in the
Elisp / Emacs / ... manuals."


